**What problem or use case are you trying to solve?**

In https://github.com/All-Hands-AI/OpenHands/pull/9738, we are trying to implement model routing.

But it is challenging to define a clean interface that mimics `LLM`, because `LLM.completion` currently receives `messages` that with multimodal content removed by `conversation_memory.process_events` --> making it not possible to implement the `MultimodalRouter` without passing raw `events` into then:

https://github.com/All-Hands-AI/OpenHands/pull/9738/files/1803afbc0228a0eef55affd4ac770ea6f017fcb7#diff-87161bc5e5878424ca3e735946431d1bb9e68848182337e2b40ecda12f6b119cR11

**Describe the UX or technical implementation you have in mind**

We should refactor to move `vision_is_active` check from `conversation_memory.process_events` to `LLM` class, so that we can refind our model router to follow this pattern here:

```
llm_registry = LLMRegistry()

class CompositeLLM(LLM):

	def completion(*args, **kwars):
	    # we do model routing logic here

class MultimodalModelRouter(CompositeLLM):
	def completion(messages: list[Message]):
	  # do some classification
		has_multmodal_content: bool = False
		for message in messages:
			if message.contains_vision():
				has_multmodal_content = True

		if has_multmodal_content:
			return self.primary_llm(messages)
		else:
			return self.secondary_llm(messages)

llm: CompositeLLM = llm_registry.get_router(
   primary="gpt5",
   secondary="sonnet"
)
agent = Agent(llm=llm, tools=tools)
```

